CREATE MODEL `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-2-project_id']}}.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-2-dataset_id']}}.model_{{$.pipeline_job_uuid}}`
      OPTIONS (
          model_type = 'ARIMA_PLUS',
          time_series_timestamp_col = '{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}',
          time_series_id_col = '{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}}',
          time_series_data_col = '{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}}',
          horizon = @forecast_horizon,
          auto_arima = True,
          auto_arima_max_order = @max_order,
          data_frequency = @data_granularity_unit,
          holiday_region = 'GLOBAL',
          clean_spikes_and_dips = True,
          adjust_step_changes = True,
          decompose_time_series = True
      ) AS
      SELECT
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}},
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}},
      FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-uri']}}`
      WHERE
        UPPER({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}}) IN UNNEST(@splits)
        AND TIMESTAMP({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) < @start_time

WITH
        fractional_splits AS (
          SELECT
            percentiles[OFFSET(@train_percent)] AS train_split,
            percentiles[OFFSET(@validation_percent)] AS validation_split,
          FROM (
            SELECT APPROX_QUANTILES(DISTINCT {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}, 100) AS percentiles,
            FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--get-first-valid-Output']}}`
          )
        ),
        numbered_data_with_fractional_splits AS (
          SELECT
            data.*,
            CASE
              WHEN {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}} < train_split THEN 'TRAIN'
              WHEN {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}} < validation_split THEN 'VALIDATE'
              ELSE 'TEST'
            END AS _{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}},
            DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) - 1 AS window_number,
          FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--get-first-valid-Output']}}` AS data
          CROSS JOIN fractional_splits
        ),
        data_with_fractional_splits_and_windows AS (
          SELECT
            *,
            IF(
              MOD(window_number, @window_stride) = 0
                AND RAND() < @window_freq,
              TRUE,
              FALSE
            ) AS _{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}}
          FROM numbered_data_with_fractional_splits AS data
        )
      SELECT
        CAST({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}} AS STRING)
          AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}},
        TIMESTAMP({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        CAST({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}} AS FLOAT64) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}},
        COALESCE({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-3-Output']}}, _{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}}) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}},
        COALESCE(
          {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-5-Output']}}, _{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}}
        ) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}},
      FROM data_with_fractional_splits_and_windows

WITH
        time_series_windows AS (
          SELECT
             FIRST_VALUE({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) OVER (horizon) AS start_time,
             COUNT(*) OVER (horizon) AS count,
             FIRST_VALUE({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}}) OVER (horizon) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}},
           FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-uri']}}`
           WHERE UPPER({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}}) IN UNNEST(@splits)
           WINDOW horizon AS (
             PARTITION BY {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}}
             ORDER BY {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}
             ROWS BETWEEN 0 PRECEDING AND @forecast_horizon FOLLOWING)
        )
      SELECT
        start_time,
        TIMESTAMP(DATETIME_ADD(
          DATETIME(start_time),
          INTERVAL @forecast_horizon {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--data_granularity_unit']}}
        )) AS end_time,
        SUM(count) AS count,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER () AS window_number,
      FROM time_series_windows
      WHERE {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-4-Output']}}
      GROUP BY start_time

CREATE TABLE `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-project_id']}}.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-dataset_id']}}.metrics` (
              predicted_on_{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}} TIMESTAMP,
              MAE FLOAT64,
              MSE FLOAT64,
              MAPE FLOAT64,
              prediction_count INT64
            )

CREATE TABLE `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-project_id']}}.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--bigquery-create-dataset-dataset_id']}}.evaluated_examples` (
              {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}} STRING,

              predicted_{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}} STRUCT<value FLOAT64>
            )

SELECT
        SUM(MAE * prediction_count) / SUM(prediction_count) AS MAE,
        SQRT(SUM(MSE * prediction_count) / SUM(prediction_count)) AS RMSE,
        SUM(MAPE * prediction_count) / SUM(prediction_count) AS MAPE,
      FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-2-uri']}}`

          holiday_region = 'GLOBAL',
          clean_spikes_and_dips = True,

          decompose_time_series = True
      ) AS
      SELECT
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}},
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}},
      FROM `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-uri']}}`
      WHERE
        UPPER({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--maybe-replace-with-default-2-Output']}}) IN UNNEST(@splits)
        AND TIMESTAMP({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) < @start_time

SELECT
        @start_time AS predicted_on_{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        AVG(mean_absolute_error) AS MAE,
        AVG(mean_squared_error) AS MSE,
        AVG(mean_absolute_percentage_error) AS MAPE,
        @prediction_count AS prediction_count,
      FROM ML.EVALUATE(
        MODEL `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--query-with-retry-Output']}}`,
        TABLE `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-uri']}}`,
        STRUCT(True AS perform_aggregation, {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--forecast_horizon']}} as horizon))

SELECT
        actual.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}},
        TIMESTAMP(actual.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}}) AS {{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        @start_time AS predicted_on_{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}},
        actual.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}},
        STRUCT(pred.forecast_value AS value) AS predicted_{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--target_column_name']}},
      FROM
        ML.FORECAST(
          MODEL `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--query-with-retry-Output']}}`,
          STRUCT({{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--forecast_horizon']}} AS horizon)) pred
      JOIN `{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--table-to-uri-uri']}}` actual
         ON
           pred.forecast_timestamp = TIMESTAMP(actual.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_column']}})
           AND pred.{{$.inputs.parameters['pipelineparam--time_series_identifier_column']}}

def bigquery_delete_dataset_with_prefix(
    project: str,
    location: str,
    dataset_prefix: str,
    delete_contents: bool = False,
) -> None:
  """Deletes all BigQuery datasets matching the given prefix."""
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  from google.cloud import bigquery
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  client = bigquery.Client(project=project, location=location)
  for dataset in client.list_datasets(project=project):
    if dataset.dataset_id.startswith(dataset_prefix):
      client.delete_dataset(
          dataset=dataset.dataset_id,
          delete_contents=delete_contents)

import kfp
from kfp.v2 import dsl
from kfp.v2.dsl import *
from typing import *

def bigquery_list_rows(
    project: str,
    location: str,
    table: dsl.Input[dsl.Artifact],
) -> List[Dict[str, str]]:
  """Lists the rows of the given BigQuery table.

  Args:
    project: The GCP project.
    location: The GCP region.
    table: A google.BQTable artifact.

  Returns:
    A list of dicts representing BigQuery rows. Rows are keyed by column, and
    all values are stored as strings.
  """
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  from google.cloud import bigquery
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  client = bigquery.Client(project=project, location=location)
  metadata = table.metadata
  rows = client.list_rows('.'.join(
      [metadata['projectId'], metadata['datasetId'], metadata['tableId']]))
  result = []
  for row in rows:
    result.append({col: str(value) for col, value in dict(row).items()})
  return result

import kfp
from kfp.v2 import dsl
from kfp.v2.dsl import *
from typing import *

def build_preprocessing_query_parameters(
    training_fraction_split: float = 0,
    validation_fraction_split: float = 0,
    window_stride_length: int = 1,
    window_max_count: int = 1e8,
    row_count: int = 1,
) -> list:  # pylint: disable=g-bare-generic
  """Creates configuration JSON objects for the split column query.

  All query parameters will be stored in a list of QueryParameter objects:
  https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/QueryParameter

  Args:
    training_fraction_split: Fraction of the data to use for training.
    validation_fraction_split: Fraction of the data to use for validation.
    window_stride_length: Period to use when selecting test samples to map to
      evaluation windows. A stride of 1 will result in one window per timestamp.
    window_max_count: Maximum number of windows across the entire dataset. Used
      to determine the frequency to sample the test data when creating windows.
    row_count: The number of rows in the dataset.

  Returns:
    A list of QueryParameters.
  """
  return [
      {
          'name': 'train_percent',
          'parameterType': {'type': 'INTEGER'},
          'parameterValue': {'value': str(int(training_fraction_split * 100))},
      },
      {
          'name': 'validation_percent',
          'parameterType': {'type': 'INTEGER'},
          'parameterValue': {
              'value': str(int(
                  (training_fraction_split + validation_fraction_split) * 100)),
          },
      },
      {
          'name': 'window_stride',
          'parameterType': {'type': 'INTEGER'},
          'parameterValue': {'value': str(window_stride_length or 1)},
      },
      {
          'name': 'window_freq',
          'parameterType': {'type': 'FLOAT'},
          'parameterValue': {
              'value': str(min(1.0, (window_max_count or 1e8) / row_count)),
          },
      },
  ]

def count_rows(
    project: str,
    location: str,
    table: str
) -> int:
  """Returns the number of rows in the given table.

  Args:
    project: The GCP project.
    location: The GCP region.
    table: The BigQuery table to get a row count for.

  Returns:
    The number of rows in the given table.

  Raises:
    AssertionError: If the query did not return a single row.
  """
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  from google.cloud import bigquery
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  client = bigquery.Client(project=project, location=location)
  rows = client.query(f'SELECT COUNT(*) AS count FROM `{table}`').result()
  assert rows.total_rows == 1, f'Only 1 result expected, got {rows.total_rows}.'
  return int(next(rows).count)

def generate_iso8601_underscore_datetime_format(run_id: str) -> str:
  """Creates a timestamp using the same logic as Vertex Forecasting."""
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  import datetime
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  timestamp = datetime.datetime.now().strftime('%Y_%m_%dT%H_%M_%S_%f')[:23]
  return f'{run_id}_{timestamp}Z'

import kfp

from kfp.v2.dsl import *
from typing import *

def load_table_from_uri(
    project: str,
    location: str,
    source_uris: List[str],
    destination: str,
    source_format: str = 'CSV',
) -> str:
  """Creates a table from a list of URIs.

  Args:
    project: The GCP project.
    location: The GCP region.
    source_uris: URIs of data files to be loaded; in format
      gs://<bucket_name>/<object_name_or_glob>.
    destination: Table into which data is to be loaded.
    source_format: The file format for the files being imported. Only CSV is
      supported.

  Returns:
    The destination table containing imported data.
  """
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  from google.cloud import bigquery
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  if not source_uris:
    return ''

  client = bigquery.Client(project=project, location=location)
  job_config = bigquery.LoadJobConfig(
      autodetect=True, source_format=source_format)
  client.load_table_from_uri(
      source_uris=source_uris,
      destination=destination,
      project=project,
      location=location,
      job_config=job_config).result()
  return destination

          'validation_fraction_split',
          'test_fraction_split',
          'predefined_split_column',

  )(

      result.get('validation_fraction_split', 0.0),

def query_with_retry(
    project: str,
    location: str,
    query: str,
    query_parameters: list,  # pylint: disable=g-bare-generic
    job_configuration_query: dict,  # pylint: disable=g-bare-generic
    max_retry_count: int = 5,
    retry_wait_seconds: int = 10,  # Waits up to 4 minutes before 5th retry.
    destination_uri: str = '',
) -> str:
  """Runs a query and retries on failure.

  Args:
    project: The GCP project.
    location: The GCP region.
    query: The query to run.
    query_parameters: A list of query parameters.
    job_configuration_query: Additional query job configurations.
    max_retry_count: Maximum number of times to retry the query.
    retry_wait_seconds: Approximate initial number of seconds to wait before
      making another query attempt with exponential backoff.
    destination_uri: Optional BigQuery URI to output if the query succeeds.

  Returns:
    The given destination URI.
  """
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  import logging
  import random
  import time

  from google.api_core import exceptions
  from google.cloud import bigquery
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  client = bigquery.Client(project=project, location=location)
  job_configuration_query['queryParameters'] = query_parameters
  job_config = bigquery.QueryJobConfig.from_api_repr(
      {'query': job_configuration_query})
  retry_count = 0
  while True:
    try:
      client.query(query, job_config=job_config).result()
      break
    except exceptions.Forbidden as e:
      if retry_count >= max_retry_count:
        logging.info('Maximum retries reached.')
        raise
      wait_time = (
          retry_wait_seconds * (2 ** retry_count) * random.uniform(1, 1.5))
      logging.info(
          'Query failed with %s. Retrying after %d seconds.', e, wait_time)
      time.sleep(wait_time)
      retry_count += 1
  return destination_uri

import kfp
from kfp.v2 import dsl
from kfp.v2.dsl import *
from typing import *

def validate_inputs(
    time_column: Optional[str] = None,
    time_series_identifier_column: Optional[str] = None,
    target_column_name: Optional[str] = None,
    bq_source: Optional[str] = None,
    training_fraction_split: Optional[float] = None,
    validation_fraction_split: Optional[float] = None,
    test_fraction_split: Optional[float] = None,
    predefined_split_column: Optional[str] = None,
    gcs_source: Optional[List[str]] = None,
    source_model_uri: Optional[str] = None,
    bigquery_destination_uri: Optional[str] = None,
    window_column: Optional[str] = None,
    window_stride_length: Optional[int] = None,
    window_max_count: Optional[int] = None,
) -> None:
  """Checks training pipeline input parameters are valid."""
  # pylint: disable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel
  import re
  # pylint: enable=g-import-not-at-top,import-outside-toplevel

  project_pattern = r'([a-z0-9.-]+:)?[a-z][a-z0-9-_]{4,28}[a-z0-9]'
  dataset_pattern = r'.[a-zA-Z0-9_]+'
  table_pattern = r'.[^\.\:`]+'

  # Validate BigQuery column and dataset names.
  bigquery_column_parameters = [
      time_column,
      time_series_identifier_column,
      target_column_name,
  ]
  column_pattern = re.compile(r'[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]{1,300}')
  for column in bigquery_column_parameters:
    if column is not None and not column_pattern.fullmatch(column):
      raise ValueError(f'Invalid column name: {column}.')
  dataset_uri_pattern = re.compile(project_pattern + dataset_pattern)
  if (
      bigquery_destination_uri != '-'
      and bigquery_destination_uri is not None
      and not dataset_uri_pattern.fullmatch(bigquery_destination_uri)
  ):
    raise ValueError(
        f'Invalid BigQuery dataset URI: {bigquery_destination_uri}.')
  table_uri_pattern = re.compile(
      project_pattern + dataset_pattern + table_pattern)
  if (
      source_model_uri is not None
      and not table_uri_pattern.fullmatch(source_model_uri)
  ):
    raise ValueError(f'Invalid BigQuery table URI: {source_model_uri}.')

  # Validate data source.
  data_source_count = sum([bool(source) for source in [bq_source, gcs_source]])
  if data_source_count > 1:
    raise ValueError(f'Expected 1 data source, found {data_source_count}.')
  if bq_source and not table_uri_pattern.fullmatch(bq_source):
    raise ValueError(f'Invalid BigQuery table URI: {bq_source}.')
  gcs_path_pattern = re.compile(r'gs:\/\/(.+)\/([^\/]+)')
  if gcs_source:
    for gcs_path in gcs_source:
      if not gcs_path_pattern.fullmatch(gcs_path):
        raise ValueError(f'Invalid path to CSV stored in GCS: {gcs_path}.')

  # Validate split spec.
  fraction_splits = [
      training_fraction_split,
      validation_fraction_split,
      test_fraction_split,
  ]
  split_count = sum(
      [bool(source)
       for source in [predefined_split_column, any(fraction_splits)]])
  if split_count > 1:
    raise ValueError(f'Expected 1 split type, found {split_count}.')
  if (
      predefined_split_column
      and not column_pattern.fullmatch(predefined_split_column)
  ):
    raise ValueError(f'Invalid column name: {predefined_split_column}.')
  if any(fraction_splits):
    if not all(fraction_splits):
      raise ValueError(
          f'All fractions must be non-zero. Got: {fraction_splits}.')
    if sum(fraction_splits) != 1:
      raise ValueError(
          f'Fraction splits must sum to 1. Got: {sum(fraction_splits)}.')

  # Validate window config.
  window_configs = [window_column, window_stride_length, window_max_count]
  window_config_count = sum([bool(config) for config in window_configs])
  if window_config_count > 1:
    raise ValueError(f'Expected 1 window config, found {window_config_count}.')
  if window_column and not column_pattern.fullmatch(window_column):
    raise ValueError(f'Invalid column name: {window_column}.')
  if window_stride_length and (
      window_stride_length < 1 or window_stride_length > 1000):
    raise ValueError('Stride must be between 1 and 1000. Got: '
                     f'{window_stride_length}.')
  if window_max_count and (window_max_count < 1000 or window_max_count > 1e8):
    raise ValueError('Max count must be between 1000 and 100000000. Got: '
                     f'{window_max_count}.')
